<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="1373" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1373">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Germamy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-05T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1624. At suggestion Ambassador at Constantinople bring immediately to the
                            notice of the German Government that he has been making every effort to
                            persuade Sublime Porte not to expose non-combatant British and French
                            subjects to bombardment at Dardanelles. Ambassador has pleaded with
                            German Ambassador to use his influence, but received no assurances of
                            assistance. German Ambassador informed him that as two English submarine
                            boats are <pb facs="1228" n="970" xml:id="pg_970"/> in the Marmora, some
                            belligerents would henceforth be placed on every Turkish transport ship.
                            As deportation to the Dardanelles is contemplated for Thursday, the
                            matter is urgent.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>